         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers0431">
               <p>Coats was a native of <placeName>Scotland</placeName> who became a <seg
                     ana="itinerancy">traveling preacher</seg> in <date when="1741">1741</date>. He
                  had a gift for languages, having studied Gaelic, Danish, and Dutch in addition to
                  Greek, Hebrew, and Latin. At the time of his death, <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> referred to him as &apos;the
                  oldest preacher in our connexion&apos;. See Atmore, <hi rend="italic"
                     >Memorial</hi>, 75. On the spelling of his last name, see <hi rend="italic"
                     >Works</hi>, 10:281 n 981.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
